<faion_clarification>
  <status>needs_clarification</status>

  <context>
{{ context }}
  </context>

  <instruction_to_main_agent>
The faion subagent could not confidently pick methodology files because the user's task is ambiguous.
Do this in the main session:
  1. Use the AskUserQuestion tool to ask the user the questions below. Pass `header`, `question`, `multi_select`, and `options` exactly as given.
  2. After the user answers, summarise their answers as a short user-style message in the conversation so that the next /faion invocation sees them in the transcript.
  3. Re-invoke `/faion` (or run `python3 ~/workspace/projects/faion-net/faion-network/skills/faion/scripts/retrieve.py "$CLAUDE_SESSION_ID"`). The subagent will now have enough context to return a bundle.
Do NOT attempt to answer the questions yourself. Do NOT proceed to other work until clarification is collected.
  </instruction_to_main_agent>

  <questions>
{% for q in questions %}
    <question header="{{ q.header | e }}" multi_select="{{ 'true' if q.multi_select else 'false' }}">
      <text>{{ q.question | e }}</text>
{% for opt in q.options %}
      <option label="{{ opt.label | e }}"{% if opt.description %} description="{{ opt.description | e }}"{% endif %}/>
{% endfor %}
    </question>
{% endfor %}
  </questions>
</faion_clarification>
